      { question: 'How many countries does EuroSalary cover?', answer: 'EuroSalary currently provides salary data for 27 EU countries: Germany, France, Netherlands, Belgium, Luxembourg, Austria, Ireland, Spain, Italy, Portugal, Finland, Sweden, Denmark, Poland, and Czech Republic. We add new countries quarterly as verified data becomes available.' },
      { question: 'How does the EU Pay Transparency Directive affect my company?', answer: 'The EU Pay Transparency Directive (2023/970) requires employers to disclose salary ranges in job postings and report gender pay gaps. Member states must transpose the directive into national law by June 2026. EuroSalary helps you generate compliant pay bands and disclosure templates for every country you operate in.' },
